rComments: Amazing professor who was very knowledgeable, and willing to help. The content in CHM362 is easy, but VERY hard to memorize all reactions, cycles, pathways, mechanisms, enzymes and what not. The course itself is just extremly hard, but the professor did her best to make it easy and stream line down to just what was important.
She was pretty good this year. She was very helpful in office hours and her marking was really easy! Have to write the final in a couple weeks so we'll see...

It's not an easy course for sure. The course started really well and she was really good for the first half of the course. After that, she started rushing the course to get everything done before the end of the semester. :(...She expects you to work hard and marks fair.I probably learned the most in her class out of all my courses!
Really helpful enthusiastic prof.  She's very smart and expects you to think.  Don't take the course if you want an easy A but if you are going to work it is worth it.
